<task id="020" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D2-11 Chat-pane orchestration UX (file chips, "N files attached" indicator, per-file remove, inline confirmations, multi-file interjection)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 day</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort></actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration</phase>
    <wave>P2-G5 (parallel — UI orchestration alongside 019 + 021 + 022)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>017</dependencies>
    <tags>frontend, chat, ux, react-19</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend the existing R3 `ConversationPane.tsx` chat surface with the R5 session-files
    orchestration UX. The R5 vertical slice ("Summarize a Document") requires that the
    Assistant input area surface uploaded files as chips, expose a persistent "N files
    attached" indicator, support per-file removal that cascades to BOTH the
    `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]` server manifest AND the `spaarke-session-files` AI
    Search index, render inline confirmations in the chat thread when files become
    ready, and inject a deterministic (NOT LLM-generated) interjection when the user
    requests a combined summary of multiple files — appearing once per multi-file
    summary turn, clarifying that all files will be combined.

    This task is purely frontend orchestration: the `useChatFileAttachment` hook
    (`@spaarke/ui-components/SprkChat/hooks`) already produces validated chip state
    and the R4 `handleAttachmentReady` callback already dispatches a Workspace
    widget_load event for the first attachment. R5 builds on top of these by wiring
    the chip lifecycle to the new R5 server manifest + index cleanup path and adding
    the chat-side affordances (indicator, confirmations, interjection,
    `context.files_staged` dispatch). NO new component is introduced — `SprkChat` +
    `ConversationPane` are extended in-place per the R5 reuse mandate.

    Critical-path member: task 020 sits between 017 (StructuredOutputStreamWidget) and
    031 (Phase 2 verification) on the project critical path. Slow or buggy chat-pane
    file UX blocks the entire vertical-slice verification.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend engineer with deep Fluent UI v9 + React 19 experience and a
    working understanding of the Spaarke `@spaarke/ui-components` SprkChat surface
    (especially `useChatFileAttachment` chip semantics), the SpaarkeAi shell
    `PaneEventBus` typing, and the R5 server contracts (`ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]`
    manifest, session-files index document IDs in `SearchDocumentIdsCsv`).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ConversationPane.tsx` (+ SprkChat-side chip helpers if delta is minimal) renders
    the following R5-only behaviour on the SpaarkeAi shell:

    1. File chips visible in the Assistant input area on upload (existing
       `useChatFileAttachment` chip strip — confirm dark-mode + accessibility intact).
    2. A persistent "N files attached" indicator rendered NEAR the input area
       (visible whenever `ChatSession.UploadedFiles.length &gt; 0`, not just while
       chips are extracting). Updates reactively as files are added / removed.
    3. A per-file remove affordance on each chip that, when clicked:
       (a) calls `useChatFileAttachment.removeFile(index)` (existing in-memory
           splice — preserved behaviour);
       (b) dispatches a chat-session manifest removal to the BFF (per task 004's
           manifest contract);
       (c) triggers session-files index document removal via the cleanup pathway
           established by task 007 (call the cleanup endpoint or BFF-side service
           the cleanup job exposes — confirm pathway in Step 3 below).
    4. Inline file-confirmation messages appear in the chat thread when files become
       `status === 'ready'` — e.g., "I have your 3 files: a.pdf, b.docx, c.md".
       These are LOCAL (client-rendered) messages, NOT model-generated; one
       confirmation per upload turn (debounced across simultaneous arrivals).
    5. When the user requests a combined-summary turn over multiple files (slash
       command `/summarize` with `UploadedFiles.length &gt; 1`, OR a free-text
       summarize request with multiple files in manifest), a deterministic
       interjection is injected ONCE per turn before the model response begins —
       e.g., "I'll combine all 3 files into a single summary."
    6. PaneEventBus dispatches `context.files_staged` (new ADR-030 event type added
       by task 016) when files transition to ready. Existing
       `handleAttachmentReady` Workspace dispatch is preserved (R4 task 042 / W-4
       behaviour MUST NOT regress).
    7. Dark mode + Fluent v9 semantic tokens enforced — no hardcoded colors.

    Acceptance criteria below codify each behaviour as a testable contract.
  </goal>

