  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 reuse mandate (project CLAUDE.md §3.1)">MUST extend existing `ConversationPane` + `SprkChat`. MUST NOT introduce a parallel chat pane or duplicate the existing `useChatFileAttachment` chip lifecycle. Cite the existing component reuse in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 — hooks + functional components only; no class components; no React 18-only APIs; no module-level side effects.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 — semantic tokens (`tokens.*`) only; no hardcoded colors; dark mode MUST work without visual regression. Use `makeStyles` + `mergeClasses` per existing `ConversationPane` style block.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shared component boundary — `useChatFileAttachment` lives in `@spaarke/ui-components`; SpaarkeAi shell MUST NOT import any SpaarkeAi-specific telemetry / auth back INTO the shared lib. The R5 cleanup wiring (manifest + index DELETE) lives in the SpaarkeAi shell layer (or in a SpaarkeAi-side service consumed by `ConversationPane`), NOT inside `useChatFileAttachment`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">PaneEventBus channels closed at 4 — task adds NO new channels. R5 dispatches additive event types only: `context.files_staged` (this task wires the dispatch; the event type definition lands via task 016).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Auth v2 — chat-session manifest DELETE + index cleanup invocations MUST use the existing `@spaarke/auth` token acquisition path (fresh token per request; never snapshot tokens in closures). No new auth boundary surfaces in this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">R5 introduces NO new feature flags (per project CLAUDE.md §3.2). Chip-render behaviour is unconditional; do NOT gate this UI behind a new flag.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-03 (prompt-first path)">Multi-file combined-summary interjection MUST be deterministic — generated client-side by the R5 chat-pane code, NOT by the model. Appears exactly once per multi-file summary turn (no duplicate emission on resubmission, retry, or stream resumption).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-02">Hard cap of 20 uploaded files per session is enforced upstream by `useChatFileAttachment` (which enforces MAX_ATTACHMENTS = 5 per turn) + server-side manifest. This task respects the cap and reports "N files attached" accurately for `N &lt;= 20`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project CLAUDE.md §3.7">Frontend test obligation — task MUST add Jest/RTL tests for the new affordances (indicator render, per-file remove dispatch, interjection emission, PaneEventBus dispatch). Tests colocated with `ConversationPane.tsx` per existing pattern.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">BFF publish-size: this is a frontend-only task. BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (confirm in task notes; no BFF code modified).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No regression of R4 `handleAttachmentReady` Workspace dispatch (the existing `workspace.widget_load` for the first file MUST continue firing; this task only ADDS a parallel `context.files_staged` dispatch).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Inline file-confirmation messages MUST be tagged as local/client-rendered (e.g., via the existing `SprkChat` message metadata field if available, or a R5-only local-message convention). They MUST NOT be persisted as model-generated turns in `ChatSession.Messages` server-side.</constraint>
  </constraints>

