  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">File chips appear in the Assistant input area when the user uploads files (existing `useChatFileAttachment` behaviour preserved; dark-mode + a11y verified).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">A persistent "N files attached" indicator renders near the input area whenever `UploadedFiles.length &gt; 0` (or `attachments.length &gt; 0` per Step 3 decision); reactively updates on add/remove; hidden when N = 0.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-file remove action on a chip cascades to: (a) `useChatFileAttachment.removeFile(index)`; (b) `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]` manifest removal via the BFF; (c) `spaarke-session-files` index document removal via the cleanup pathway from task 007. All three legs verified end-to-end in an integration scenario (or mocked-HTTP unit test for legs (b) + (c)).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Inline file-confirmation messages appear in the chat thread as local (client-rendered) messages when files transition to `status === 'ready'` — one consolidated message per upload batch (debounced); NOT persisted server-side as model-generated turns.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Multi-file combined-summary deterministic interjection (e.g., "I'll combine all N files into a single summary") emits exactly ONCE per multi-file summarize turn — verified across normal, retry, and stream-resumption scenarios. Single-file summarize turns do NOT emit the interjection.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PaneEventBus dispatches `context.files_staged` with a correctly-typed payload (per task 016's `PaneEventTypes.ts`) on ready transitions. R4 `workspace.widget_load` dispatch for the first ready file STILL fires (regression-tested).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Dark mode + a11y verified — indicator contrast ≥ 4.5:1 in both themes; chip remove keyboard-accessible; before/after screenshots captured in task notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Jest + RTL tests added covering indicator render, remove cascade (with mock HTTP), inline confirmation debounce, interjection single-emission, PaneEventBus dispatch, R4 regression. Tests green; ≥ 90% line coverage on new paths.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build --workspace SpaarkeAi` succeeds without new TypeScript errors or React 19 / Fluent v9 warnings.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (frontend-only task) OR if Step 3 surfaced a tiny new endpoint: delta &lt; +0.5 MB and recorded in task notes per project CLAUDE.md §3.6.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5. ADR-012 / ADR-021 / ADR-022 / ADR-028 / ADR-030 + project CLAUDE.md §3.7 compliance verified.</criterion>
